10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Hedge funds</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a sense in which the main sto=
ry of modern hedge funds is style drift. You start out doing convertible ar=
bitrage or merger arb or relative-value structured-credit trades, you make =
a lot of money, you attract more investors, you gain in confidence at the s=
ame time that you reach the limits of your strategy=E2=80=99s capacity, you=
 expand into other strategies, you make more money, you conclude that you a=
re an all-purpose genius, you start going on television, your returns maybe=
 suffer a bit but who cares, and you end up trying to influence national po=
litics and/or <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2656=
1018.257624/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1TQ0NmazJhMk81bw/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb3747e39" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">mentoring Diddy</a>.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Arguably this works best for your clients at the early sta=
ges, when you are making them a lot of money by focusing on your fairly spe=
cialized core skills. There is a long <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/26561018.257624/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vYXJ0aWN=
sZS91cy1oZWRnZWZ1bmRzLWFja21hbi1leGNsdXNpdmUvZXhjbHVzaXZlLWFja21hbi1jdXRzLX=
N0YWZmLXNodW5zLWxpbWVsaWdodC1hcy1oZS1zZWVrcy10by10dXJuLWFyb3VuZC1mdW5kLWlkV=
VNLQk4xRkIzMlk_X190d2l0dGVyX2ltcHJlc3Npb249dHJ1ZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
42d57b9f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">history</a> of clients <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/26561018.257624/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEtMTgvYmxhY2tyb2NrLXN0aWxsLWxpa2VzLWNhcGl0YWx=
pc20_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cm=
NlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMjAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfb50c446" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> complaining</a> that their hedge fu=
nd managers go on TV too much. But surely it works best for=C2=A0<em>you=C2=
=A0</em>at the later stages, when you are rich and hanging out with Diddy. =
Starting a hedge fund is not <em>only</em>=C2=A0a bet that, if you work har=
d and have lots of skill and get a bit lucky, you will make a lot of money =
and win the respect of your peers and the gratitude of your clients. Starti=
ng a hedge fund is also a bet that you might get famous.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">Arguably then it is a valuable service to hedge fund clients =
to promise them that their managers will not get famous? Here=E2=80=99s Nis=
hant Kumar at Bloomberg News on <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/26561018.257624/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlY=
XR1cmVzLzIwMjItMDEtMzAvdG9wLWhlZGdlLWZ1bmRzLWNpdGFkZWwtbWlsbGVubml1bS1zaGlm=
dC00LXRyaWxsaW9uLXNlY3Rvci1mcm9tLXJvY2stc3RhcnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwMTIyX01PTkV=
ZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09Mj=
IwMjAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB36c9d9bb" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> multi-strategy funds</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Investors are plowing money into funds that don=E2=80=99t rely on the ne=
xt macro genius or star stockpicker, but instead offer an army of traders w=
ho invest in an array of strategies. These behemoths secured pretty much al=
l of the new money in the hedge fund industry last year, cementing a tecton=
ic shift that=E2=80=99s accelerated since the pandemic.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Clients are increasingly willing to pay high fees =E2=
=80=94 outsized even by hedge fund standards =E2=80=94 to gain access to a =
whole universe of investments, from U.S. stocks and precious metals to Asia=
n currencies, executed by scores of traders who can be easily replaced if t=
hey stumble.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a stark con=
trast to the old business model: Launch a fund, name it after yourself, cal=
l the shots, profit. A generation of managers are finding this new style mo=
re appealing =E2=80=94 and in some cases have little choice since flashy tr=
ading stars aren't in vogue with investors any more. With a shakeout underw=
ay in an industry that runs about $4 trillion, multi-strats are the only wa=
y to grow.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Byrne Hobart =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26561018.257624/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGlmZi5jby9wL3BvZC1wZW9wbGU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3947=
2281" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">points out</a> that one advantage of a multi-strategy=C2=A0<e=
m>fund=C2=A0</em>is that it more tightly limits=C2=A0<em>managers=C2=A0</em=
>to one strategy:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Pod shop mana=
gers lose other kinds of flexibility, too. Since they're all trying to deli=
ver uncorrelated alpha, the fund has to make sure correlations don't sneak =
into their various portfolios. One way to do this is to impose very specifi=
c limitations on what a given manager can invest in, and how their portfoli=
o can be positioned.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If =
you are a convertible arbitrage portfolio manager at a multi-strategy fund,=
 and you decide that your genius for financial markets is such that you sho=
uld also dabble in emerging-markets currencies, your boss will just tell yo=
u no. Your job is to add uncorrelated alpha, and you have to do your job.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a convertible arbitrage m=
anager at your own fund, you are the boss, and it is not so clear what your=
 job is. One thing that I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/26561018.257624/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjEtMDgtMjQvaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd2FudC10by1zdGF5LXBvcHVsYXI_Y21waWQ9Qk=
JEMDIwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0Z=
XImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMjAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB2b645383" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> often say</a> about managing a hedge fund is that =
the primary job is not picking stocks that go up, but rather=C2=A0continuin=
g to manage a hedge fund. If you are a hedge fund manager and you=E2=80=99r=
e down 20% one year, but your investors do not withdraw much money because =
(1) they like you or (2) you wrote a really good investor letter explaining=
 your losses with a lot of well chosen quotes from classical philosophers o=
r=C2=A0(3) they have signed long-term lockups or (4) you have structured a =
permanent capital vehicle, then you had a pretty good year all things consi=
dered! So your job is to be liked, to write good letters, to negotiate lock=
ups, to structure permanent capital vehicles, etc., as much as it is to add=
 uncorrelated alpha. If you go to work for a multi-strategy fund none of th=
at works:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Multi-strats, meanwhi=
le, have a low tolerance for underperformance. With individual managers les=
s visible to clients, those who start losing in high single digits or overe=
xtend their risk can have their assets cut at best, and at worst can be fir=
ed on the spot.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The good=
 news, for the portfolio managers, is that you get to focus on investing. K=
umar:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CJoining a multi-=
strat on Monday and having $500 million to punt around on Tuesday is a hell=
 of lot more appealing than scrounging for $50 million of seed capital to s=
tart your own firm,=E2=80=9D Andrew Beer, founder of New York-based Dynamic=
 Beta Investments, said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And H=
obart:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A platform fund is part =
of this evolution for the hedge fund business: most people who start funds =
don't do it because they have a deep and abiding love of back-office operat=
ions, risk management, and investor relations. They do it because they like=
 predicting which way asset prices will go, and <em>really</em> like gettin=
g paid for it.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you got into=
 the hedge fund business because you are really good at predicting asset pr=
ices in a particular niche, and you want to focus on that,=C2=A0then multi-=
strategy funds are appealing. If you got into the hedge fund business becau=
se you=E2=80=99re really good at raising money from investors, and you want=
 to be famous, then you will want and need to strike out on your own. If yo=
u are an investor, which sort of hedge fund manager would you want to inves=
t with?</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cel=
lpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
