s helps the economy grow. More to the point, the=C2=A0<em>withdrawal=C2=A0<=
/em>of credit by banks hurts the economy, and the risk here is wrong-way. I=
f people get nervous about banks and pull out all their money to put it in =
safer stablecoins, then (1) that will probably happen at a time when the ec=
onomy is shaky and (2) that will definitely make the economy shakier. The b=
ulk of the response to the 2008 financial crisis involved=C2=A0<em>preventi=
ng runs on banks</em>, because those would have made all of the problems of=
 the crisis much worse.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suspect that this=
